cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image generation and transformation. The use of GANs and Capsule networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of geometric transformations and 3D image generation suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the experimentation with performance control and training stability suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
